50|$|For larger {{production}} quantities, continuous vacuum fryers are available. In these installations, {{the vacuum}} frying pan is {{installed in a}} stainless steel vacuum tube. The infeed of the raw product is carried out through a rotary airlock.Depending on the application, the frying pan itself is {{designed to meet the}} different product specifications. A transport belt takes the finished product out of the fryer and towards the <b>outfeed</b> <b>system.</b> A lock chamber at the exit of the vacuum tube prevents air from entering the vacuum zone, and a belt system takes the product from one zone to another.|$|E

